# DifferentOS

A lightweight Arch-based Linux system setup script that automates the installation and configuration of essential packages and system settings.

> ⚠️ **Note:** This project is still in development and is primarily available for personal testing and cloning. Please excuse any errors or incomplete features.

## What it does

DifferentOS is a Bash-based automation script for setting up an Arch-based Linux environment with:
- Essential package installation (fastfetch, fish shell, git)
- System welcome message (MOTD) customization
- Shell configuration (switches default shell to fish)

## Quick Start

Clone the repository and run the installation script:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Todesengel-Tamino/DifferentOS.git
cd DifferentOS
bash run-install.sh
